<HL>
   Business Brief -- Nicron Resources Ltd.:
   Aztec Mining Co. of Sydney
   Bids for All of Mining Firm
</HL>
<DATE>
07/13/90
</DATE>
<SO>
WALL STREET JOURNAL (J), PAGE B4A
</SO>
<CO>
   AMX
</CO>
<IN>
TENDER OFFERS, MERGERS, ACQUISITIONS (TNM)
</IN>
<LP>
   Aztec Mining Co. Ltd. of Sydney, Australia, which is 49.4%
owned by U.S. metals and energy company Amax Inc., yesterday
said it is bidding for all of Nicron Resources Ltd., an
Australian mining company.
   Aztec said in a statement it already owns 19.99% of Nicron
Resources.
</LP>
<TEXT>
   Aztec is offering shareholders four Aztec shares for every
five shares in Nicron Resources. The offer, which isn't
subject to a minimum acceptance condition. requires
regulatory approval.
   If the takeover offer is successful, Amax's shareholding
in Aztec will be diluted to 33.2%, the company said.
   Aztec said it holds naturalized status in terms of
Australia's foreign investment policy.
   Aztec has 62% of Bounty Gold Mine and 20% of the Scuddles
Zinc Mine, both in Western Australia.
   Aztec also has interests in a number of other base metal
and gold exploration projects, including 24% of the Chessy
Copper zinc project in France.
</TEXT>
